===Etymology===
From {{L.}} '''[[Laconicus|Lacōnicus]]''' "Spartan" < {{AGr.}} '''{{polytonic|[[Λακωνικός]]}}''' (Lakōnikos) "Laconian". Laconia was the region surrounding and ruled by the Spartans, who were known for their brevity in speech.

